replies.body:
If Darius had no mana, he'd just be able to spam his strong harass combo all the time whenever it was off cooldown.

See, that's unbalanced, and League doesn't have any of tho- 

{{champion:92}}

To limit him. He sucks with Mana items because he has such a great synergy with {{item:3071}} and {{item:3065}} . Those 2 give 30% CDR.
His mana cost stays relevant for the entire game, so he can't keep healing with Q forever.
{{summoner:31}}

Yup. I actually dropped Darius for soloq, your team has to kinda work around you post early game.
But that's the theorie behind it.
{{summoner:31}}

I think it goes something like this:
"Do we want this champion to spam their abilities constantly?"
Cooldowns only- abilities are generally weak to compensate their constant use. {{champion:86}} {{champion:55}} {{champion:92}} 

"Do we want this champion to use their abilities often to create a unique playstyle?"
Energy/Fury/Heat/Health- abilities are stronger but also give larger windows of opportunity in order to prevent as much spamming. {{champion:64}} {{champion:266}} {{champion:68}} 

"Do we want this champion to have powerful ability to make a (Comparatively) massive difference whenever they're used?"
Mana- forcing the champion to conserve their resources to make the ability count. {{champion:99}} {{champion:90}} {{champion:91}}
